This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it deals with data consistency and synchronization in large scale distributed systems. It could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category as it discusses CRDTs and their synchronization algorithms. Additionally, it could be classified under Databases (cs.DB) as it deals with data consistency and synchronization. The System and Control (cs.SY) sub-category is also a possibility as it discusses fault-tolerance. Finally, the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category could be relevant as it deals with synchronization in a network graph.
